#800000;">bray</span></x-word> when he <x-word word="hath"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #FF0000;">hath</span></x-word> grass? or <x-word word="loweth"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #0000FF;">loweth</span></x-word> the <x-word word="ox"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #FF0000;">ox</span></x-word> over his <x-word word="fodder"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #FF0000;">fodder</span></x-word>?<br>野驴有草岂能叫唤？牛有料岂能吼叫？<br><br><br>伯6:6 <br>Can that which is <x-word word="unsavoury"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #800000;">unsavoury</span></x-word> be eaten without salt? or is there any taste in the white of an egg?<br>物淡而无盐岂可吃吗？蛋青有什么滋味呢？<br><br><br>伯6:7 <br>The things that my soul refused to touch are as my <x-word word="sorrowful"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #800000;">sorrowful</span></x-word> meat.<br>看为可厌的食物，我心不肯挨近。<br><br><br>伯6:8 <br>Oh that I might have my request; and that God would grant me the thing that I long for!<br>惟愿我得着所求的，愿 神赐我所切望的：<br><br><br>伯6:9 <br>Even that it would please God to destroy me; that he would <x-group group="letXloose"><span style="box-shadow: 0px 3px white, 0px 4px #00BFFF;">let loose</span></x-group> his hand, and cut me off!<br>就是愿 神把我压碎，伸手将我剪除。<br><br><br>伯6:10 <br>Then should I yet have comfort; <x-word word="yea"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #800000;">yea</span></x-word>, I would <x-word word="harden"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #FF0000;">harden</span></x-word> myself in <x-word word="sorrow"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #FF0000;">sorrow</span></x-word>: let him not spare; for I have not concealed the words of the Holy One.<br>我因没有违弃那圣者的言语，就仍以此为安慰，在不止息的痛苦中还可踊跃。<br><br><br>伯6:11 <br>What is my strength, that I should hope? and what is mine end, that I should <x-word word="prolong"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #FF0000;">prolong</span></x-word> my life?<br>我有什么气力使我等候？我有什么结局使我忍耐？<br><br><br>伯6:12 <br>Is my strength the strength of stones? or is my flesh of <x-word word